GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 834
Short Title: Sportsman's Voter Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Almond, N. Jackson, and Huneycutt (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Election Law, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 10, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE EACH PERSON SEEKING A HUNTING OR FISHING LICENSE IN
3 THIS STATE BE OFFERED AN OPPORTUNITY TO REGISTER TO VOTE AND TO
4 PARTICIPATE IN THE ORGAN DONOR REGISTRY.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. G.S. 113-275 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
7 "(l) A person applying for any license under this Article shall be offered an opportunity
8 to register to vote pursuant to G.S. 163-82.19 and to participate in the Organ Donor Registry
9 internet site established pursuant to G.S. 20-43.2. After consultation with the State Board of
10 Elections and the Division of Motor Vehicles, the Wildlife Resources Commission shall adopt
11 rules for compliance with this subsection."
12 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025, and applies to licenses issued
13 under Chapter 113 of the General Statutes on or after that date.
*H834-v-1*

